description:
In src/main.rs lines 757-773, the cursor blink timer runs unconditionally every 530ms, calling cx.notify() and triggering a re-render even when:
- The window is hidden
- No text input is focused
- The app is not in use

This wastes CPU cycles and battery. The timer should be gated to only run when:
1. WINDOW_VISIBLE is true
2. A text input is focused (focused_input is MainFilter, ArgPrompt, or ActionsSearch)

Suggested fix:
```rust
loop {
    Timer::after(std::time::Duration::from_millis(530)).await;
    let _ = cx.update(|cx| {
        this.update(cx, |app, cx| {
            // Only blink cursor when window is visible and input is focused
            if !WINDOW_VISIBLE.load(Ordering::SeqCst) {
                return;
            }
            if app.focused_input == FocusedInput::None {
                return;
            }

            app.cursor_visible = !app.cursor_visible;
            // ... rest of the logic
            cx.notify();
        })
    });
}
```

Impact: Low priority performance optimization - reduces unnecessary renders when idle.

In src/main.rs line 2522, the `render_toasts` method calls cx.notify() during the render cycle:

```rust
fn render_toasts(&mut self, cx: &mut Context<Self>) -> Option<impl IntoElement> {
    // Tick the manager to handle auto-dismiss
    self.toast_manager.tick();

    // Clean up dismissed toasts
    self.toast_manager.cleanup();

    // Check if we need to re-render
    if self.toast_manager.take_needs_notify() {
        cx.notify();  // Line 2522 - Called during render!
    }
    // ...
}
```

While this has a guard (`take_needs_notify()` should return false on subsequent calls), calling cx.notify() during render() is an anti-pattern that can:
1. Cause unnecessary render cycles
2. Make debugging render performance harder
3. Potentially cause subtle timing issues

Better approach: Use a separate timer/watcher to check toast state and call notify() outside of render, similar to how the cursor blink timer works.

Impact: Low priority - the current code works due to the guard, but should be refactored for cleaner architecture.
